cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning human-object interaction from video. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the importance of embodied visual intelligence, which is relevant to robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a new approach to learning human-object interaction. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of machine learning to anticipate object interaction. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the value of grounding affordances in real human-object interactions, which is relevant to HCI.
